after some investigation, this is likely the cause of the weight instability. TLDR; validator using a future timestamp

Issue: https://github.com/macrocosm-os/mainframe/blob/e71b0dfbbf410460f8ff1c2fa5237424798ccdc6/neurons/validator.py#L667

**a validator that has a different timestamp, say UTC+5**
- the validator creates  "future jobs" in batches with timestamp that are 5 hrs ahead
- jobs are stored in the shared database with these future timestamps
- in the reward loop, the validator queries `updated_at (UTC) >= {last_time_checked} (UTC+5)`
- the validator would only find and update its own completed jobs

**other validators**
- for the next 5hrs, other validators reward the completed "future jobs" due to `updated_at (UTC+5) >= {last_time_checked} (UTC)` until they caught up with the timestamp.
- EMA gets hit with large explosion / decay
- (screenshot below shows how the weight setting fluctuates every ~5 hr, noticing that RT21 validator is not affected)

quick fix:
make sure all validator uses the same timezone.
last check RT21 still producing UTC+5 jobs. probably need to restart validator after correcting the timezone to UTC @CapriciousSage 

perm fix:
update all `datetime.now()` in validator code to use `datetime.now(timezone.utc)`
